org.spongepowered.api

Interface Server


  • public interface Server
    Represents a typical Minecraft Server.

      • getWorldProperties

        Optional<WorldProperties> getWorldProperties(String worldName)
        Gets the WorldProperties of a world. If a world with the given name is loaded then this is equivalent to calling World.getProperties(). However, if no loaded world is found then an attempt will be made to match unloaded worlds.
        Parameters:
        worldName - The name to lookup
        Returns:
        The world properties, if found

      • getWorldProperties

        Optional<WorldProperties> getWorldProperties(UUID uniqueId)
        Gets the WorldProperties of a world. If a world with the given UUID is loaded then this is equivalent to calling World.getProperties(). However, if no loaded world is found then an attempt will be made to match unloaded worlds.
        Parameters:
        uniqueId - The UUID to lookup
        Returns:
        The world properties, if found

      • unloadWorld

        boolean unloadWorld(World world)
        Unloads a World, if there are any connected players in the given world then no operation will occur.

        A world which is unloaded will be removed from memory. However if it is still enabled according to WorldProperties.isEnabled() then it will be loaded again if the server is restarted.

        Parameters:
        world - The world to unload
        Returns:
        Whether the operation was successful

      • createWorldProperties

        WorldProperties createWorldProperties(String folderName,
                                      WorldArchetype archetype)
                               throws IOException
        Creates a new WorldProperties from the given WorldArchetype. For the creation of the WorldArchetype please see WorldArchetype.Builder.

        If the World exists at the folder name given, the properties representing that folder name are returned instead.

        Although the world is created it is not loaded at this time. Please see one of the following methods for loading the world.

        • loadWorld(String)
        • loadWorld(UUID)
        • loadWorld(WorldProperties)
        Parameters:
        folderName - The name of the folder for the world
        archetype - The archetype for creation
        Returns:
        The new or existing world properties, if creation was successful
        Throws:
        IOException - If there are any io issues creating the properties file

      • copyWorld

        CompletableFuture<Optional<WorldProperties>> copyWorld(WorldProperties worldProperties,
                                                       String copyName)
        Creates a world copy asynchronously using the new name given and returns the new world properties if the copy was possible.

        If the world is already loaded then the following will occur:

        • World is saved.
        • World saving is disabled.
        • World is copied.
        • World saving is enabled.
        Parameters:
        worldProperties - The world properties to copy
        copyName - The name for copied world
        Returns:
        An Optional containing the properties of the new world instance, if the copy was successful

      • renameWorld

        Optional<WorldProperties> renameWorld(WorldProperties worldProperties,
                                      String newName)
        Renames an unloaded world.
        Parameters:
        worldProperties - The world properties to rename
        newName - The name that should be used as a replacement for the current world name
        Returns:
        An Optional containing the new WorldProperties if the rename was successful

      • getServerScoreboard

        Optional<Scoreboard> getServerScoreboard()
        Gets the 'server' scoreboard. In Vanilla, this is the scoreboard of dimension 0 (the overworld).

        The server scoreboard is used with the Vanilla /scoreboard command, automatic score updating through criteria, and other things.

        The server scoreboard may not be available if dimension 0 is not yet loaded. In Vanilla, this will only occur when the server is first starting, as dimension 0 is normally always loaded.

        Returns:
        the server scoreboard, if available.

      • getChunkLayout

        Returns:
        The chunk layout used by the implementation

      • getRunningTimeTicks

        int getRunningTimeTicks()
        Gets the time, in ticks, since this server began running for the current session.

        This value is not persisted across server restarts, it is set to zero each time the server starts.

        Returns:
        The number of ticks since this server started running

        For the Sponge implementation on the client, this will trigger the Integrated Server to shutdown a tick later.

      • getTicksPerSecond

        double getTicksPerSecond()
        Gets the current ticks per second. A tick represents one cycle of the game loop.

        Note: The server aims to limit itself at 20 ticks per second. Lower ticks per second may elude to the server taking more time to process information per tick. Examples of overburdening the server per tick include spawning 10,000 cows in a small area.

        Returns:
        The current ticks per second

      • getDefaultResourcePack

        Optional<ResourcePack> getDefaultResourcePack()
        Gets the default resource pack. The default resource pack is sent to players when they join the server.
        Returns:
        The default resource pack

      • getPlayerIdleTimeout

        int getPlayerIdleTimeout()
        Gets the player idle timeout, in minutes.

        A return value of 0 disables the player idle timeout.

        Returns:
        The player idle timeout

      • setPlayerIdleTimeout

        void setPlayerIdleTimeout(int timeout)
        Sets the player idle timeout, in minutes.

        A value of 0 disables the player idle timeout.

        Parameters:
        timeout - The player idle timeout

      • isMainThread

        boolean isMainThread()
        Checks if the current thread matches the main thread of the server.
        Returns:
        True if main thread, false if not
